Package: fishblicc
Title: Bayesian Length Interval Catch Curve
Version: 0.0.0.1000
Authors@R: 
    person("Paul", "Medley", , "paulahmedley@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: The package provides functions for fitting a catch curve to length frequency data. The model assumes that the fish population is in a steady state (constant recruitment), growth is Gamma distributed with a fixed CV and mean following the von Bertalanffy function and mortality is constant within each length interval. The model provides the expected frequency in each length interval for a negative binomial likelihood. This implementation assumes that natural mortality is constant and selectivity can be modelled using a double-sided normal function. The model is fitted using Stan which estimates the probability for parameters of interest. 
